 tech valuation. He tried to take it public, failed, was ousted with a gian=
t payout, and went off to start a new company called Flow that is roughly W=
eWork but apartments. (Apartment rentals, happy hours, vibes, patter, ventu=
re capitalist investors.)
Meanwhile WeWork went bankrupt without Neumann=E2=80=99s patter (that may n=
ot actually be the reason), and Neumann started talking about maybe buying =
it back. Last month he apparently submitted a $500 million bid. I have no i=
dea how seriously to take any of this, because =E2=80=9Chow serious is this=
=E2=80=9D is always the wrong question with Adam=C2=A0Neumann, but last wee=
k Ben Bergman at Business Insider interviewed him=C2=A0and asked =E2=80=9Cw=
hat's the likelihood you think you'll be successful at acquiring WeWork?=E2=
