One possibility is that you should try to make your writing sound like a la=
rge language model wrote it:
=09Having an LLM write your stuff demonstrates that you understand how to u=
se LLMs, which is perhaps the most useful general business skill in 2024.=
=09Probably an LLM is going to=C2=A0read=C2=A0your stuff, to summarize it f=
or your actual audience, so=C2=A0having it sound like an=C2=A0LLM=C2=A0make=
s it more legible and persuasive.=09Even if a human does read your stuff, p=
robably that human is reading a lot of LLM-generated text these days, so sh=
e=E2=80=99ll find your stuff more legible and persuasive if it sounds like =
an LLM.

Another possibility is that you should try to make your writing sound like =
a large language model did=C2=A0not=C2=A0write it:
=09It=E2=80=99s artisanal, you know? The human touch?=09Venture capitalists=
 love contrarianism, and I suppose that these days generating text without =
an LLM is a bit contrarian.

