10px;">
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Not everything is securities fraud</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CEverything is securities fraud,=E2=80=
=9D I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35042113.285=
343/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDItMDM=
vZ29sZG1hbi1zYWNocy1nb2VzLXRvLXN1cHJlbWUtY291cnQtaGVkZ2UtZnVuZHMtd29uLW9uLW=
dhbWVzdG9wLWtrcG9lNndzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA0MTUyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09Z=
W1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDQxNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249=
bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9e614b01" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">like to say</a> a=
round here, meaning:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Sometimes a public company does a bad=
 thing, or has a bad thing happen to it.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom:=
 5px;">News of the bad thing comes out and the stock drops.</li>=09<li styl=
e=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Shareholders sue, saying =E2=80=9Cyou didn=E2=80=
=99t tell us about the bad thing in advance, so we bought the stock thinkin=
g there was no bad thing, but then we found out that there was a bad thing.=
 We were defrauded; we overpaid for the stock because of your lies.=E2=80=
=9D</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Occasionally I add a technical clarification: =
Simply=C2=A0<em>not mentioning=C2=A0</em>a bad thing is not fraud=C2=A0unde=
r US securities law. The law (<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusines=
s.com/click/35042113.285343/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGF3LmNvcm5lbGwuZWR1L2Nmci90ZXh=
0LzE3LzI0MC4xMGItNQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB789510d5" itemprop=3D"StoryLin=
k" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Rule 10b-5</=
a>) says that it=E2=80=99s fraud =E2=80=9Cto make any untrue statement of a=
 material fact or to omit to state a material fact necessary in order to ma=
ke the statements made, in the light of the circumstances under which they =
were made, not misleading.=E2=80=9D So=C2=A0<em>lying=C2=A0</em>=E2=80=94=
=C2=A0saying something that isn=E2=80=99t true =E2=80=94=C2=A0is securities=
 fraud. And many=C2=A0<em>omissions=C2=A0</em>are securities fraud, if the =
company omits information that is =E2=80=9Cnecessary in order to make the s=
tatements made =E2=80=A6=C2=A0not misleading.=E2=80=9D (So <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35042113.285343/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYm=
xvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDUtMDEvaXQtZG9lc24tdC1wYXktd=
G8tYmUtdG9vLWV0aGljYWw_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQxNTI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1l=
bWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNDE1JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1=
tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBed624bab" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">for instance</a> i=
f a company=E2=80=99s public statements say =E2=80=9Cwe have an ethics poli=
cy and try to be ethical,=E2=80=9D and omit to mention =E2=80=9Cour executi=
ves did an unethical thing,=E2=80=9D somebody will sue over that, claiming =
that the description of the ethics policy was misleadingly positive.)</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But it is not securities fraud=C2=A0<em>simply=
 </em>not to mention a bad thing. If a bad thing happens, and the company d=
oesn=E2=80=99t say anything about it, and it doesn=E2=80=99t say anything t=
hat might be misleading, that=E2=80=99s not securities fraud. This does not=
 come up that often, because companies are always going around saying gener=
ic things that might be contradicted by their bad news. If a company has a =
sexual harassment scandal, its statements about its ethics policy might be =
misleading; if it has a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/=
click/35042113.285343/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljb=
GVzLzIwMjMtMTAtMzEvYmFkLXBhc3N3b3Jkcy1hcmUtc2VjdXJpdGllcy1mcmF1ZD9jbXBpZD1C=
QkQwNDE1MjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHR=
lciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA0MTUmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cB967b53c5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_=
blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;">computer hack</a>, its statements about its inform=
ation security policy might be misleading; etc. But in theory pure silence =
is not securities fraud.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still, you could imagine pure silence being mi=
sleading. For instance, you could imagine things that the market would=C2=
=A0<em>expect to be disclosed=C2=A0</em>if they happened, so that=C2=A0<em>=
not=C2=A0</em>disclosing them sort of implies that they didn=E2=80=99t happ=
en. If a company=E2=80=99s chief executive officer died suddenly, and the c=
ompany=C2=A0didn=E2=80=99t tell anyone=C2=A0for a few weeks, that would be =
weird! The company hasn=E2=80=99t <em>lied</em>, but everyone kind of went =
around assuming that the CEO was alive, and the company didn=E2=80=99t both=
er to correct their mistaken impression.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or: There are a lot of US Securities and Excha=
nge Commission rules requiring companies to disclose certain things. <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35042113.285343/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cubGF3LmNvcm5lbGwuZWR1L3dleC9yZWd1bGF0aW9uX3Mtaw/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cBec68e9e6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;">Regulation S-K</a>, for instance, requires companies=
 to disclose certain specific=C2=A0types of information about their busines=
s in their quarterly filings: Companies are <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/35042113.285343/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGF3LmNvcm5lbGwuZ=
WR1L2Nmci90ZXh0LzE3LzIyOS4zMDM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB98687999" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
supposed to</a>=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cdescribe any known trends or uncertainties th=
at have had or that are reasonably likely to have a material favorable or u=
nfavorable impact on net sales or revenues or income from continuing operat=
ions,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Cdescribe briefly any material <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35042113.285343/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGF3LmN=
vcm5lbGwuZWR1L2Nmci90ZXh0LzE3LzIyOS4xMDM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf680db6a"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">pending legal proceedings</a>,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35042113.285343/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGF3LmNvcm5l=
bGwuZWR1L2Nmci90ZXh0LzE3LzIyOS4xMDU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb3caefb4" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;">discuss</a> =E2=80=9Cmaterial factors that make an investment in the re=
gistrant or offering speculative or risky,=E2=80=9D etc.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If the law says that you have to disclose any =
material lawsuits in your quarterly report on Form 10-Q, and there is some =
material lawsuit against you, and you file a 10-Q and don=E2=80=99t mention=
 the lawsuit, then that is arguably misleading. =E2=80=9CIf there was a law=
suit, they would be required to mention it, and they didn=E2=80=99t mention=
 a lawsuit, so there must not be one,=E2=80=9D investors could reasonably c=
onclude. The omission,=C2=A0<em>combined with the reporting requirement</em=
>, is misleading. If Form 10-Q consisted of a literal form with a box sayin=
g =E2=80=9CAre there any material lawsuits against you,=E2=80=9D and you wr=
ote =E2=80=9Cno,=E2=80=9D the =E2=80=9Cno=E2=80=9D would be a false stateme=
nt. Arguably just leaving out the required disclosure has the same effect.<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/35042113.285343/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc3VwcmVtZWNvdXJ0Lmdvdi9Eb=
2NrZXRQREYvMjIvMjItMTE2NS8yOTM4NjcvMjAyMzEyMjAxNDEyMjY0NDRfMjItMTE2NWFjJTIw=
TWFjcXVhcmllJTIwdi4lMjBNb2FiJTIwUGFydG5lcnMucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa=
547e96e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">that is the view</a> of the US Securities and Exchange Com=
mission:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">An MD&amp;A [management=E2=80=99s discussion a=
nd analysis] that makes certain statements but omits information that [Regu=
lation S-K] Item 303 requires to be included is a misleading half-truth.=C2=
=A0... By filing an MD&amp;A describing certain known trends and uncertaint=
ies, an issuer makes statements. If the issuer omits other known trends or =
uncertainties that meet Item 303=E2=80=99s threshold, the MD&amp;A=E2=80=99=
s statements will be misleading to a reasonable investor, who will be aware=
 of Item 303=E2=80=99s requirement to list all material known trends or unc=
ertainties, and therefore will assume that the MD&amp;A provides a complete=
 list. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Where regulatory disclosure requirements apply=
, reasonable investors will infer from an issuer=E2=80=99s silence that the=
 types of events for which disclosure is required have not occurred.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Macquarie Infrastructure Corp. operated termin=
als for=C2=A0No. 6 fuel oil. In 2016, the United Nations essentially banned=
 No. 6 fuel oil by 2020. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/35042113.285343/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc3VwcmVtZWNvdXJ0Lmdvdi9vcGluaW9ucy8y=
M3BkZi8yMi0xMTY1XzEwbjIucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfd94239c" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">But=
</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the ensuing years, Macquarie di=
d not discuss IMO 2020 [the UN ban] in its public offering documents. In Fe=
bruary 2018, however, Macquarie announced a drop in the amount of storage c=
ontracted for use by its subsidiary due in part to the decline in the No. 6=
 fuel oil market. Macquarie=E2=80=99s stock price fell 41%.</p></blockquote=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Shareholders naturally sued, arguing that (1) =
Regulation S-K=C2=A0required Macquarie to =E2=80=9Cdescribe any known trend=
s or uncertainties that have had or that are reasonably likely to have a ma=
terial favorable or unfavorable impact on net sales or revenues or income f=
rom continuing operations,=E2=80=9D (2) this was a known trend or uncertain=
ty that was likely to be bad for sales, (3) Macquarie did not disclose it a=
nd (4) that was misleading. Macquarie argued that it couldn=E2=80=99t be se=
curities fraud just to=C2=A0<em>not mention=C2=A0</em>the new UN rule. The =
district court agreed and dismissed the lawsuit, but an appeals court disag=
reed, finding that, when there=E2=80=99s a rule requiring disclosure of som=
ething, it can be fraud not to disclose the thing.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Macquarie appealed to the Supreme Court, and l=
ast Friday it won. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/35042113.285343/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc3VwcmVtZWNvdXJ0Lmdvdi9vcGluaW9ucy8yM3BkZi=
8yMi0xMTY1XzEwbjIucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCfd94239c" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">The unani=
mous Supreme Court said</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The question in this case is wheth=
er the failure to disclose information required by Item 303 can support a p=
rivate action under Rule 10b=E2=80=935(b), even if the failure does not ren=
der any =E2=80=9Cstatements made=E2=80=9D misleading. The Court holds that =
it cannot. Pure omissions are not actionable under Rule 10b=E2=80=935(b).</=
p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess that is the better reading of the actu=
al words of the rule, though it is a weird reading of its intent. Omitting =
things that you=E2=80=99re required to disclose really does seem misleading=
.=C2=A0In any case, there you go, some things are not securities fraud.</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
></ol>
