<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One possibility is that you should try to make=
 your writing sound like a large language model wrote it:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Having an LLM write your stuff demonst=
rates that you understand how to use LLMs, which is perhaps the most useful=
 general business skill in 2024.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">P=
robably an LLM is going to=C2=A0<em>read=C2=A0</em>your stuff, to summarize=
 it for your actual audience, so=C2=A0having it sound like an=C2=A0LLM=C2=
=A0makes it more legible and persuasive.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom:=
 5px;">Even if a human does read your stuff, probably that human is reading=
 a lot of LLM-generated text these days, so she=E2=80=99ll find your stuff =
more legible and persuasive if it sounds like an LLM.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another possibility is that you should try to =
make your writing sound like a large language model did=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0<=
/em>write it:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It=E2=80=99s artisanal, you know? The =
human touch?</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Venture capitalists l=
ove contrarianism, and I suppose that these days generating text without an=
 LLM is a bit contrarian.</li>
</ul>
